Usage: create_bump_grid [-help] -grid_name <string> -layers <string>
                        -origin {x y} -pitch {x y}

-help                   # Prints out the command usage
-grid_name <string>     # Specify the bump grid name (string, required)
-layers <string>        # Specify the layer names. User can set the layer of
                        # relative bump pin to this option (string, required)
-origin {x y}           # Specify the coordinates of original bump grid
                        # (point, required)
-pitch {x y}            # Specify the spacing between two bumps. The first
                        # value defines the horizontal spacing, the second
                        # value defines the vertical spacing (point, required)